The '''Agrarian Party''' (in Spanish: ''Partido Agrario'', PA) was a [[Panama]]nian small regionalist [[conservative]] [[political party]]. The party was active in [[Chiriquí Province]] in the 1920s and 1940s. <ref>''Almanaque panameño''. Editorial Balboa, 1940. Pp. 274.</ref> The PA was represented in the Panamian Parliament from 1928 to 1936. <ref>''Political Handbook of the World'', 1929. New York, 1929. Pp. 143.</ref> <ref>''Political Handbook of the World'', 1936. New York, 1936. Pp. 146.</ref>
[[Carlos V. Biebarach]] (later a justice of the Supreme Court of [[Panama]]) and [[Manuel C. Díaz Armuelles]] were the founders and leaders of the Party. <ref>Clyde Schubert Stephens. Bananeros in Central America: true stories of the tropics. S.N., 1989. Pp. 105.</ref>
