{{For|the later unrelated party|Manx National Party}}

The '''National Party''' was a party in the [[Isle of Man]] that identified itself with the [[Conservative Party (UK)|UK Conservatives]].  They were active in the period between [[World War I]] and [[World War II]] in opposing the activities of the [[Manx Labour Party]]. However, unlike the Manx Labour Party, they were unsuccessful in establishing themselves over the longer term and they folded.

